Hello to you Cllaude271. To begin with, I do not take LSD.
I think you should just see another doctor or a toxicologist (I don't know if that's the exact term)
If after 5 months you still have this kind of "side effect" it's really bad.
So without wanting to panic you should go see a toxicologist who I think will prescribe you a treatment or emergency medication.
Otherwise there are helplines or specialised forums. Good luck. Peace
Hello Cllaude271,
To have been through the state you describe (following mixing with bavards, micropointes, taz, keta, and everything else that passed through),
if I can give you a piece of advice it's just to tell you that all of this is just psychological.
Basically, the more you worry about these states, the worse they will become.
A very simple thing in these cases, you take deep breaths, you breathe slowly, and you settle in a place where you feel safe, and not too close to the walls (yes sometimes you can feel like they are closing in on you).
After several months of use, especially when you mix things, you can experience effects, especially after a sudden stop of the substances.
Don't worry, it's just a matter of time.
But as Claude532 said, consulting a psychiatrist can also help you get rid of those voices that are cluttering your head.
Keep the faith, and stay positive.
Thank you both for your answers
I will try to be patient,
